========================================================
           TestNG DataProvider - Quick Revision Notes
========================================================

What is DataProvider?

• DataProvider is a Method in TestNG.
• It is used to pass Multiple Sets of Data to a Single @Test Method.
• It supports Data-Driven Testing.

========================================================
Rules to Remember
========================================================

Step 1:
DataProvider is denoted by the @DataProvider annotation.

Syntax:
@DataProvider(name = "LoginData1")

--------------------------------------------------------

Step 2:
A DataProvider Method Always Returns Data.

Return Type:
• Object[][]
• String[][] (if all data is String)

Example:

public Object[][] loginData() {

    Object[][] data = {
        {"user1@gmail.com","pass1"},
        {"user2@gmail.com","pass2"}
    };

    return data;
}

--------------------------------------------------------

Step 3:
Generally, we use a Two-Dimensional Array.

Reason:
• Each Row = One Test Execution
• Each Column = One Parameter

Example:

Username              Password
----------------------------------------
sameer@gmail.com      pass123
admin@gmail.com       admin123

========================================================
Using DataProvider from Another Class
========================================================

@Test(
    dataProvider = "LoginData1",
    dataProviderClass = DataProvider_UtilityClass.class
)

public void m1(String userName, String password) {

}

========================================================
Flow of Execution
========================================================

@DataProvider
        ↓
Returns Object[][] / String[][]
        ↓
@Test(dataProvider = "LoginData1",
      dataProviderClass = DataProvider_UtilityClass.class)
        ↓
TestNG Executes the Same Test Method
Once for Every Row of Data.

========================================================
Interview Revision Points
========================================================

✔ DataProvider is a Method in TestNG.

✔ Used for Data-Driven Testing.

✔ It passes Multiple Sets of Data to a Single Test Method.

✔ It always Returns Data.

✔ Return Type is generally Object[][].

✔ If all the data is String, we can also use String[][].

✔ Each Row represents One Test Execution.

✔ Each Column represents One Parameter.

✔ The Number of Columns in the DataProvider must match the Number of Parameters in the @Test Method.

✔ dataProvider = "LoginData1"
   → Specifies the Name of the DataProvider.

✔ dataProviderClass = DataProvider_UtilityClass.class
   → Used when the DataProvider is present in another Class.

✔ One DataProvider can be reused by Multiple Test Classes.

✔ This is the Recommended Approach in Hybrid Frameworks.